714858f-a.title: Manhattan: 94th Street (West) - Amsterdam Avenue
714858f-a.text:
167-163 West 94th Street, north side, east of Amsterdam Avenue.
About 1911.

714859f-a.title: Manhattan: 94th Street (West) - Amsterdam Avenue
714859f-a.text:
171 to 165 W. 94th Street, north side, east of Amsterdam
Avenue, snowing at the left center, a building that is being
converted into a Buddhist Temple by the New York Buddhist Gnurch
and which will be conducted by Hozen Seki of No. 121 W. 79th
Street.
This individual and his wife have been conducting similar
services at their home for the last year and state that this new
place of worship will be the first of its kind in the eastern
part of this country.
For a fuller uescriptive account see the New York Times of
June 3, 1958.
View No. 2 is the same from another angle.
May 9, 1938
Views 1 and 2
George D. Chinn
